abstract: Carl Hulse On Washington column examines Donald J Trump's struggle to establish connections with nation's tightly networked political elite; cites prominent Republicans' concerns over trustworthiness of candidate with non-existent political profile; notes Trump supporters see lack of connections as asset.
lead_paragraph: An unusual lack of personal familiarity with Mr. Trump is partly behind political veterans’ awkward courtship with the presumptive Republican nominee.

headline.main: ‘Who Is This Guy?’ In Connected Political World, Few Know Donald Trump
headline.print_headline: ‘Who Is This Guy?’ In Connected Political World, Few Know Trump
